21. Use ListView Widget in Flutter App Development

✅ Explanation (Exam-Oriented)

The ListView widget in Flutter is used to display a scrollable list of widgets arranged vertically.

Automatically provides scrolling
Useful for long lists (contacts, messages, items)
Can be created using:
ListView()
ListView.builder() (for dynamic lists)

//main code


import 'package:flutter/material.dart';

void main() {
  runApp(MyApp());
}

class MyApp extends StatelessWidget {
  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    return MaterialApp(
      home: ListViewExample(),
    );
  }
}

class ListViewExample extends StatelessWidget {
  final List<String> items = [
    "Item 1",
    "Item 2",
    "Item 3",
    "Item 4",
    "Item 5"
  ];

  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    return Scaffold(
      appBar: AppBar(
        title: Text("ListView Example"),
      ),
      body: ListView(
        children: items.map((item) {
          return ListTile(
            title: Text(item),
          );
        }).toList(),
      ),
    );
  }
}